market_id_dummies <- model.matrix(~ market_id - 1, data = train.DoorDash2)[, -6]
order_protocol_dummies <- model.matrix(~ order_protocol - 1, data = train.DoorDash2)[, -7]
store_primary_category_dummies <- model.matrix(~ store_primary_category - 1, data = train.DoorDash2)[, -1]
trainX <- cbind(market_id_dummies, order_protocol_dummies, store_primary_category_dummies,traindata_selected)
y <- train.DoorDash2$total_delivery_duration
groups <- c(rep(1, 5), rep(2, 6), rep(3, 70), seq(4, 19))

if(length(groups) != ncol(trainX)) {
  stop("Length of 'groups' does not match the number of columns in 'x'. Please adjust the 'groups' vector.")
}
x <- trainX[, !(colnames(trainX) %in% "total_delivery_duration")]
set.seed(123)
#cross validation
cv_group_lasso <- cv.grpreg(x, y, group = groups, penalty = "grLasso")
#get the best lambda based on the cross validation
best_lambda <- cv_group_lasso$lambda.min
print(paste("Best lambda for Group Lasso:", best_lambda))

)

lgb_train <- lgb.Dataset(data = trainX_matrix, label = trainy)

lgb_valid <- lgb.Dataset(data = testX_matrix,
                         label = testy)
#change params manully, to get the best result
params <- list(
  objective = "regression",
  metric = "rmse",
  num_leaves =35,
  learning_rate = 0.05,
  feature_fraction = 0.5,
  bagging_fraction = 0.5,
  bagging_freq = 5,
  verbose = -1
)
cv_results <- lgb.cv(
      params = params,
      data = lgb_train,
      nfold = 5,
      nrounds = 500,
      early_stopping_rounds = 10,
      verbose = -1
    )
 best_iter <- cv_results$best_iter

lgb_model <- lgb.train(
  params = params,
  data = lgb_train,
  nrounds =  best_iter, 
  valids = list(eval = lgb_valid),
)


pred6 <- predict(lgb_model, testX_matrix,
                num_iteration = best_iter)

importance_matrix <- lgb.importance(model = lgb_model)
lgb.plot.importance(importance_matrix, top_n = 30)

#Permutation Feature Importance
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
baseline_performance <- mean((predict(svr_model, newdata=testx) - testy)^2)

importance_scores <- rep(0, ncol(testx))


for (i in seq_along(importance_scores)) {

  data_permuted <- testx

  data_permuted[[i]] <- sample(data_permuted[[i]])
  

  permuted_performance <- mean((predict(svr_model, newdata=data_permuted) - testy)^2)
  

  importance_scores[i] <- permuted_performance - baseline_performance
}

names(importance_scores) <- colnames(testx)
importance_data <- data.frame(Feature = names(importance_scores), Importance = importance_scores)


top_importance_svr <- importance_data %>%
  arrange(desc(Importance)) %>%
  slice_max(order_by = Importance, n = 20)

  geom_col(fill = "blue") +

rankings <- data.frame(
  Feature = unlist(combined_features[-1]),
  Model = rep(names(combined_features)[-1], each = nrow(combined_features)),
  Rank = rep(1:nrow(combined_features), times = length(combined_features) - 1)
)

features_with_counts <- rankings %>%
  group_by(Feature) %>%
  summarize(
    Frequency = n(),  
    AverageRank = mean(Rank, na.rm = TRUE)
  ) %>%
  filter(Frequency >= 4) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(AverageRank = round(AverageRank, 2)) %>%
  arrange(AverageRank)

library(gains)

gains_list <- list(
  gains(valid.DoorDash2$total_delivery_duration, pred1), # MLR
  gains(valid.DoorDash2$total_delivery_duration, pred2), # Regression Tree
  gains(valid.DoorDash2$total_delivery_duration, pred3), # Random Forest
  gains(valid.DoorDash2$total_delivery_duration, pred4), # Gradient Boosting
  gains(valid.DoorDash2$total_delivery_duration, pred5), # XGBoost
  gains(valid.DoorDash2$total_delivery_duration, pred6), # LightGBM
  gains(valid.DoorDash2$total_delivery_duration, pred7)  # SVR
)

total_cases <- sum(valid.DoorDash2$total_delivery_duration)
total_obs <- dim(valid.DoorDash2)[1]

plot(0, type = "n", xlim = c(0, total_obs), 
     ylim = c(0, total_cases), 
     xlab = "# cases", ylab = "Cumulative delivery duration", main = "Lift Chart")
lines(x = c(0, total_obs), y = c(0, total_cases), col="gray", lty=2)

colors <- rainbow(7)
model_names <- c("MLR", "Reg Tree", "RF", "GBM", "XGBoost", "LightGBM", "SVR")
for(i in 1:length(gains_list)) {
  gain <- gains_list[[i]]
  lines(c(0, gain$cume.obs), c(0, gain$cume.pct.of.total * total_cases), 
        col = colors[i], lwd = 2)
}
legend("bottomright", legend = model_names, col = colors, lwd = 2, cex = 0.8)
